solutions.content:
**Approach 1: Using Dijkstra[TLE]**
It happen to be the same idea of Dijkstra's algorithm, but we need to keep the path. 
*We consider current cost or not but we have to keep the track of path cost*. As currently it's higher but for some other path we may get the minimum value at some other nodes(stops),considering this current cost. Consider Below Example for more clearity.

***Code:***
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findCheapestPrice(int n, vector<vector<int>>& flights, int src, int dst, int k) {
        // Approach 1: Using Dijksrta[TLE]
         vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n];
        // prepare an adjacency list
        for(int i = 0; i < flights.size(); i++){
            int u = flights[i][0];
            int v = flights[i][1];
            int w = flights[i][2];
            adj[u].push_back({v,w});
        }

        // create a distence vetor
        vector<int> disTo(n+1,INT_MAX);
        disTo[src] = 0;  // src is the source node

        priority_queue< pair<int,pair<int, int>>, vector<pair<int,pair<int, int>>>,greater<pair<int,pair<int,int>>> > pq;

        pq.push({0,{src,k+1}}); // {cost,{node,remainedStops}}

        while(!pq.empty())
        {
            int cost = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second.first;
            int remStops = pq.top().second.second;
            pq.pop();

            if(node == dst){
                 return disTo[dst];
            }
            if(remStops == 0){
                 continue;
            }

            for(auto it: adj[node])
            {
                int next = it.first;
                int nextDis =it.second;

                 if((cost + nextDis) < disTo[next]){
                 disTo[next] = cost + nextDis;
                }
                pq.push({cost + nextDis,{next,remStops-1}}); 
          // We consider current cost or not but we have to keep the track of path cost, 
          // As currently it's higher but for some other path we may get the minimum value at some other nodes(stops),considering this current cost.
            }
        }

        if(disTo[dst] == INT_MAX) return -1;
        return disTo[dst];
    }
};
```
*NOTE* : You can do it by Dijkstra using DP but here i will be not discussing that.

**Approach 2: Using BFS Levelwise Traversal**

***Intution*** : Since we are allowed only K stops, so either we can reach the Destination Or Not depend on value of K.
So the idea is to perform BFS K+1 times (considering src also), as we are allowed only K stops so at each level of BFS we will reach to stops with best possible cost.

**NOTE:** *We can apply this same approach to all problem where we are bounded with some threshold value, we have to find the minimum path.*

*Let's take a example for more clearity:* 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/054125b6-b556-47e2-bc46-63489468f36a_1656006744.3018532.jpeg)
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/39f275e6-8f59-437d-9035-dac5a0672c66_1656008056.9923012.jpeg)


***Code:***
```
class Solution {
public:
    // Approach 2: Level Wise BFS 
    int findCheapestPrice(int n, vector<vector<int>>& flights, int src, int dst, int k) {

         vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n];
        // prepare an adjacency list
        for(int i = 0; i < flights.size(); i++){
            int u = flights[i][0];
            int v = flights[i][1];
            int w = flights[i][2];
            adj[u].push_back({v,w});
        }

        // create a distence vetor
        vector<int> disTo(n+1,INT_MAX);
        disTo[src] = 0;  // src is the source node


        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        q.push({0,src}); // {{cost,node}}
        k = k + 1;    

        while(!q.empty())
        {

            int size = q.size();
            k--;
            if(k < 0) break;
            // Do level Wise : Traverse all stops at current level and find best path to each stop
            for(int i = 0; i < size; i++)
            {
              auto curr = q.front(); q.pop();
              int node = curr.second;
              int cost = curr.first;

              for(auto it: adj[node])
              {
                if(cost + it.second < disTo[it.first])
                {
                   disTo[it.first] = cost + it.second;
                   q.push({disTo[it.first],it.first});
                }
              }
             }
        }

        if(disTo[dst] == INT_MAX) return -1;
        return disTo[dst];
    }
};
```
