It is standard Bellman Ford  with just 2 small modifications :
1) We won't allow relaxation beyond K to make sure cheapestPrice doesn't have more than K stops
2) In each round of relaxation, changes will be done in temporary distance(price) array to ensure current path-length doesn't go beyond current iteration number. 

( For clear understanding for temp: you may take example of a linear graph with source and destination at two ends and see how normal Bellman Ford behaves if edges are arranged from source to destination vs when using temporary distance array for modifications )

