# Intuition
It is just like fibonacci series.

# Approach
In normal recursive method, the terminating case for the recursion is n = 0, n = 1, n = 2. We recursively call for n != 0 && n != 1 && n != 2 **soln(n-1) + soln(n-2) + soln(n-3)**. 

**But using this method we are repeating the calls, so let us memorize them using dp and solve.**

In the same code we make some changes and store the value in dp table.

**But using this method, recursive calls take extra space, so let us go for iterative method using dp.**

Now make a dp array and store the base cases dp[0] = 0, dp[1] = 1 and dp[2] = 1. Now from 3 to n you can just store it dp[i] = dp[i-1]+dp[i-2]+dp[i-3].

**But using this method, we are using extra space of N, so let us go for normal iterative method.**

You can see that we must only memorise the previous 3 elements so we will be storing last 3 elements.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Using normal recursion takes O(3^N)
Using recursive dp takes O(N)
Using Iterative dp takes O(N)
Using Iterative method tajes O(N) 

- Space complexity:
Using normal recursive takes O(3^N)
Using recurive dp takes O(N) + O(Recursive cost)
Using Iterative dp takes O(N)
Using Iterative method takes O(1)

