# Code - O(n) space
```
class Solution {
    public int tribonacci(int n) {
        int[] dp = new int[Math.max(n + 1, 3)];
        dp[1] = dp[2] = 1;
        for (int i = 3; i <= n; i++) {
            dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + dp[i - 2] + dp[i - 3];
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
}
```
As you can see in the code, we only look on the previous `3` variables, so we can reduce the state to O(1).

