**Recursion Solution :**

**TC --> O(3 ^ N) since 3 Recursion Calls
SC --> O(N)**

**" (Time Limit Exceeded) "**

```
class Solution {
    public int tribonacci(int n) {
        return f (n);
    }
    static int f (int n) {

        if (n == 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        if (n == 1 || n == 2) {
            return 1;
        }

        return f (n - 1) + f (n - 2) + f (n - 3);
    }
}
```

**Memoization Solution :**

`Memoization means, using an array to store the answers of calculated recursion calls, if it already calculated we just return that answers from that array, else we calculate and store in the array.`

"`Using the pre caculated answers simply means Dynamic Programming"`

**TC --> O(N)
SC --> O(N) + O(N)**


```
class Solution {
    public int tribonacci(int n) {

        int[] dp = new int[n+1];

        for (int i = 0; i < dp.length; i++) {
            dp[i] = -1;
        }  
        return f (n, dp);
    }
    static int f (int n, int[] dp) {

        if (n == 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        if (n == 1 || n == 2) {
            return 1;
        }

        if (dp[n] != -1) {
            return dp[n];
        }

        dp[n] = f (n - 1, dp) + f (n - 2, dp) + f (n - 3, dp);
        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

**Tabulation Solution :**

**TC --> O(N)
SC --> O(N)**

`This method is used to reduce the recursion stack space.`


