**General Case of Matrix Exponentiation**

So according to our equation. 
F(n) = a*F(n-1) + b*F(n-2) + c*F(n-3)

```
| F(n)   |  =  [ | a b c | ] ^ (n-2)   *  | F(2) |
| F(n-1) |     [ | 1 0 0 | ]              | F(1) |
| F(n-2) |     [ | 0 1 0 | ]              | F(0) |
```

n'th term,
    F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2) + F(n-3), n >= 3

Base Cases :
    F(0) = 0, F(1) = 1, F(2) = 1

Putting a = 1, b = 1 and c = 1 in above formula

```
| F(n)   |  =  [ | 1 1 1 | ] ^ (n-2)   *  | F(2) |
| F(n-1) |     [ | 1 0 0 | ]              | F(1) |
| F(n-2) |     [ | 0 1 0 | ]              | F(0) |
```

